               <desc type="building-data" source="#bibl000124-1">The  Zangjingidan (藏经殿) or the sutra repository of Anchansi (Song Dynasty) is built on a brick podium. The front façade is 3-bays wide and the depth is 3-bays. The central bay is twice as wide as the side bays. It has a single eaves hip-gable roof, laid with yellow and green glazed tiles with square centers. Under the eaves are four layer bracket sets (pūzuò) with a single huágŏng (petal bracket arm) and a locust head style shuătóu (trifling-tip), there is one intercolumnar bracket set in each bay. The entasis (chamfering) of the column is prominent. The original system of woodwork/latticework is no longer extant. Translated by Lydia Ohl; modified TM 7/28/10; 9/19/11; 3/2018; Edited by Cole Garrett 9/9/11, Modified by Wong Pui See, 2017.</desc>
